Package: RStataLink2
Title: NNG-Backed R and Stata Link with RStataLink-Compatible API
Version: 0.0.16.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Alek", "Rutkowski", email = "alek.rutkowski@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
  )
Description: Experimental successor to 'RStataLink' using a persistent Stata server, a Stata C plugin linked to 'libnng', and an R client using 'nanonext'. The exported R API mirrors 'RStataLink' while the internal communication machinery uses diskless NNG pair-socket messages and binary data-frame transfer.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
Roxygen: list(markdown = TRUE)
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Depends: R (>= 4.1)
Imports:
    foreign,
    nanonext,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
URL: https://github.com/alekrutkowski/RStataLink2
BugReports: https://github.com/alekrutkowski/RStataLink2/issues
SystemRequirements: Stata with plugin support; Rtools on Windows for source installation; libnng development files or cmake plus internet access for automatic bundled NNG build. Uses NNG 1.11 by default when building bundled NNG; explicitly registers NNG transports inside the Stata plugin for static-link builds.
